<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Flash news"] </F>
  [Text] According to a source in the General Staff of the 
Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF], at 1000 on 3 May KRAF units 
assigned to ensure security for the populace along Route 10 in 
Battambang Province launched a counterattack against Khmer Rouge 
[KR] forces who were plundering and torching people's houses in 
villages and communes on Route 10. 
  According to a preliminary report on the clash with the 
Khmer 
Rouge [KR], five Khmer Rouge soldiers were killed on the spot, 
and many others were wounded and were taken away by their 
comrades. The KRAF seized a T-58 tank, a car, a 76.2-mm cannon, 
a 37-mm gun, a 23-mm gun, and a large number of handguns and 
machineguns. 
  The KRAF General Staff will supply additional details about 
the situation on the battlefield later. 

