<H3> <TI>   Compromise Near on EU Semiconductor Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Compromise Near on EU Semiconductor Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0905082994 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 May 94 
Morning Edition p 9--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0905082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Nagayo Taniguchi] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 6 May -- According to an European 
diplomatic source, Japan and the European Union (EU) appear to 
have basically reached a compromise on the Japan-Europe 
semiconductor accord during an unofficial meeting held before 
summit talks by Japanese and EU leaders. They will not set a 
quota for semiconductor imports to Japan as Japan and the United 
States did. A Japanese representative said that Japan took the 
stance of accepting, as much as possible, the EU's wish to join 
the Japan-U.S. framework on research, development, and designing 
new-generation semiconductor products. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

