<H3> <TI>   Ozawa Reportedly Makes Secret Visit to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ozawa Reportedly Makes Secret Visit to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0605193394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1553 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0605193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 6 KYODO -- Ichiro Ozawa, Japan's 
behind-the-scenes power broker, clandestinely paid a three-day 
visit to Moscow without detection by the mass media, a Japanese 
diplomatic source said Friday. 
  The source told KYODO NEWS SERVICE the embassy has not 
confirmed any contacts between Ozawa and Russian politicians at 
least during the day but said he is unsure whether they were 
made at night. "Only his wife (Kazuko) and bodyguard 
accompanied him," he said. "The embassy was told that he came 
here to investigate the political and economic situation." 
  "However, in actuality, he appears to have come here for the 
sake of sightseeing and to take a rest," he said. 
  Ozawa is secretary general of Shinseito and the arch ally of 
Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata. He is credited with playing a key 
part in sweeping Hata to power. 
  In March 1991, Ozawa, then secretary general of the Liberal 
Democratic Party, flew to Moscow for talks with then Soviet 
leader Mikhail Gorbachev on such issues as the dispute on the 
sovereignty over four Russian-held islands off Japan's northern 
shore. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

