<H3> <TI>   Hata Says Yen's `Excessive Surge' Unfavorable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Says Yen's `Excessive Surge' Unfavorable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0605161594 Tokyo KYODO in English 1537 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0605161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, May 6 KYODO -- Japan's Prime Minister 
Tsutomu Hata said Friday [6 May] the recent "excessive surge" in 
the yen is unfavorable. 
  In a press conference in Brussels, Hata said he wants the 
Bank of Japan to respond to foreign exchange rate movements 
while maintaining close contact with other central banks in the 
United States and Europe. He also said exchange rates should 
properly mirror the economic fundamentals of the countries 
concerned. 
  Hata was on a six-day trip to Europe from Monday for talks 
with leaders in Italy, France, Germany and Belgium. 

</TEXT>

