discussed a military "joint countermove" of South Korea and 
Japan with the director general of the Japan Defence Agency for 
"regional security", once again taking issue with the "nuclear 
issue" of the North. And, later, the traitor Kim Yong-sam in a 
"telephone conversation" with the new Japanese prime minister, 
Tsutomu Hata, pressed home the necessity for "close cooperation" 
between Japan, South Korea and the United States for a solution 
of the "nuclear issue" of the North. 
