<H3> <TI>   Daily Urges Kim Yong-sam Group To `Step Down' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Urges Kim Yong-sam Group To `Step Down' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605055294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0511 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0605055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["NODONG SINMUN on Corruption of Kim Yong-sam Group" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim Yong-sam 
has never let a chance pass by without saying "he would not 
receive or request political funds from anyone." 
  Commenting on this, NODONG SINMUN today brands his remarks 
as 
a lie. 
  Though the traitor is still advertising his "uprightness," 
the offensive smell is coming from "Chongwadae [presidential 
office]," the analyst says, and goes on: 
  A few days ago, the president of the Democratic Party of 
South Korea told a special press conference that Kim Yong-sam 
was involved in the large-scale sangmudae political fund scandal 
which has caused quite a stir and urged him to make the case 
clear. 
  The scandal means that a big part of some 150 billion won 
earmarked for the project of the transfer of the Sangmudae 
Military Training Centre of the puppet army in Kwangju flowed 
into "Chongwadae," "the Democratic Liberal Party" and "the 
administration." 
  With the opposition party's offensive intensified over the 
scandal, "Chongwadae" and "the DLP" are now trying hard to hush 
it up. 
  Kim Yong-sam, the chieftain of corruption, is crying in 
public for "a thorough investigation into the scandal," while 
covertly manipulating the prosecution to hush it up. 
  It has been revealed once again that the "civilian" clan 
including the traitor Kim Yong-sam and his "DLP" and 
"administration" is a gang of robbers. 
  To cap it all, it has been brought to light that the second 
son of the traitor took 120 million won as a political fund from 
the Han Yang Business Relief Committee with a promise to "settle 
the public appeal." 
  With public resentment growing in this regard, "the 
civilian" 
regime is trying to shift the blame for the Sangmudae scandal on 
to "Chongwadae in the Sixth Republic" and the blame for the 
scandal related to the second son of the traitor on to the 
former "chief secretary of Chongwadae in charge of 
rectification." The traitor Kim is a master hand in dodging the 
blame by shifting it on to others. 
  The "civilian" regime's advertisement about "uprightness" 
and 
"liquidation of corruption" has fallen on the ground. The 
reality shows that the "civilian" regime is more corrupt than 
the "Fifth and Sixth Republics." 
  The Kim Yong-sam group had better step down from power 
before 
it is too late. 

</TEXT>

