<H3> <TI>   ROK Student Killed by Bullet During Training </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Student Killed by Bullet During Training </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0705044894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- The death of Chang 
Tok-su, a student of the faculty of business economics of Sejong 
University in Seoul, in a reserve force training at a puppet 
Army unit of South Korea on May 3, has turned out to have been 
caused by a live bullet, not by a blank shot as had been 
announced by the puppet Defence Ministry, according to a radio 
report from Seoul. 
  This was verified when a M-16 gun bullet was found in his 
body in an autopsy done by the Scientific Investigation 
Institute on May 5. 
  Prof. Yi Yun-song of Seoul National University, who had 
participated in the autopsy, also stated that the death of the 
student was by a live bullet. 
  The bereaved family of the student and representatives of 
Sejong University are angrily denouncing the criminal act of the 
warmaniacs and strongly demanding the resignation of the puppet 
minister of defence. 
  The General Student Council of Sejong University at a press 
conference on May 4 urged the resignation of the puppet 
minister of defence, declaring that Chang Tok-su died because of 
the unprecedentedly intensive, murderous training. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

