<H3> <TI>   South Korean Students Reported Staging Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Korean Students Reported Staging Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605050294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0453 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0605050294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Some 1,000 students in 
Jonju, South Korea, had a starting ceremony at the Jonbuk 
National University Thursday and vowed a vigorous fight to 
achieve national reunification and democracy, a radio report 
from Seoul said. 
  The starting ceremony was sponsored by the North Cholla 
Provincial Federation of General Student Councils consisting of 
general student councils of 15 universities in the province. 
  After the ceremony the students took to the streets and 
staged a protest, distributing to citizens copies of a 
literature calling for "Refusal of National Assembly endorsement 
of the final act of the Uruguay Round of world trade talks". 

</TEXT>

