<H3> <TI>   Statement of `Surviving Comfort Women' Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement of `Surviving Comfort Women' Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605050694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0605050694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- The Measure Council of 
Surviving Comfort Women for the Army of South Korea consisting 
of women who were forced to serve as "comfort women" during the 
period of the Japanese imperialist colonial rule held a press 
conference on May 3 and demanded compensation from the Japanese 
Government, a radio report from Seoul said. 
  The council declared that it would pay a protest visit to 
Japan on May 16 in case the Japanese Government failed to make 
an apology and compensation for the issue of the "comfort women 
for the army". 

</TEXT>

