<H3> <TI>   Reminiscences of Kim Il-song Published in China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reminiscences of Kim Il-song Published in China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605051094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0605051094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Vols. 1 and 2 of Part 1 
"The Anti-Japanese Revolution" of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song's reminiscences "With the Century" were published in one 
book by the social science publishing house of China in April. 
  A picture of President Kim Il-song standing on a lakeside is 
printed on the front cover of the book. 
  Carried on the front and back covers of the book are the 
propositions of President Kim Il-song "Revolutionaries, believe 
in the people and rely on them at all times and you shall always 
emerge victorious; if you are forsaken by them, you will always 
fail. Let this be your maxim in your life and struggle" and 
"The destiny of a nation can be saved only through the unity and 
struggle of all the forces that love their country and treasure 
their nation." 

</TEXT>

