Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Palestinian Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Palestinian Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0805084094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0823 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0805084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Just Efforts of Arab People for Peaceful Solution of </F>
Mideast Problem"--KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- A spokesman of the 
Foreign Ministry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
today answered the question raised by KCNA in connection with 
the recent signing of an accord on autonomy by Palestinians in 
Gaza and Jericho. 
  He said: 
  "Chairman of the Executive Committee of the Palestine 
Liberation Organisation Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhak Rabin met in Cairo on May 4 and signed an accord on 
enforcing autonomy by Palestinians in Gaza and Jericho. 
  "The accord signed this time, a detailed working agreement 
to 
implement the declaration of principle on Palestine autonomy 
which was signed in September last year, is a result of the 
patient efforts of the Palestinian people to retake the lost 
land and restore their legitimate national rights. 
  "The master of the Palestinian problem is the Palestinian 
people. 
  "We respect the will and choice of the Palestinian people in 
settling the Palestinian issue and consider signing of the 
accord by the Palestine Liberation Organisation to be their 
right. 
  "We hope the accord will be a basis of founding an 
independent state of Palestine and the first step for a fair and 
comprehensive solution to the Mideast problem. 
  "The Korean people will as ever actively support the just 
efforts of the Palestinian and Arab people for a peaceful 
solution of the Mideast problem including the Palestinian issue, 
standing on their side". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

