<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Receives More Birthday Greetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Receives More Birthday Greetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    From Foreign Party Leaders </H4>

<F P=102> SK0705052394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705052394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received messages of greetings from party 
leaders of different countries on his birthday. 
  The messages were sent by Krishna Prasad Battaray, president 
of the Central Committee of the Nepali Congress Party; Pyotr 
Simonenko, first secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Ukrainian Communist Party; Manuel Vargas Loureiro, chairman of 
the Democratic Renovation Party of Portugal; Leonel Mario Da 
Alva, chairman of the Democratic Convergence Party and Reflexion 
Group and president of the National People's Assembly of Sao 
Tome and Principe; Youssef Amin Wali, general secretary of the 
Egyptian National Democratic Party; Talal Hafun Ala Mai, general 
secretary of the People's Unity Party (Unionist) of Jordan; 
Kaled Bensmain, general secretary of the Movement for Democracy 
in Algeria; Hanial Beins, national leader of the Communist Party 
(Marxism-Leninism) of Canada; Virgilio Godoy, secretary general 
of the Independence Liberal Party of Nicaragua; Denzil Daglas, 
leader of the St. Kitts-Nevis Labour Party; and Miguel Mejia, 
secretary general of the United Left Movement of Dominica. 
  The messages sent warmest congratulations to President Kim 
Il-song and wished him good health and a long life. 
  The messages expressed firm support and solidarity for the 
Workers' Party and people of Korea in their struggle for the 
peaceful reunification of Korea. 

</TEXT>

