<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Receives More Birthday Greetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Receives More Birthday Greetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    From Meetings Held Overseas </H4>

<F P=102> SK0705052294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0436 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705052294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received congratulatory messages and 
letters from the participants in celebration meetings held in 
Corriverton, Guyana, Kalofer, Bulgaria, Weneba, Ghana, 
Antananarivo, Madagascar, and Lima, Peru, on the occasion of his 
birthday. 
  They say that President Kim Il-song has built independent 
socialism, brought great socio-economic changes and opened a new 
era of prosperity for the Korean nation by wisely leading the 
Korean revolution. 
  They note that thanks to the wise leadership and tireless 
activities of President Kim Il-song, the Korean people are 
leading a happy and creative life under the Korean-style 
socialist system centred on the popular masses and Korea has 
been turned into a powerful sovereign and independent state with 
the might of singlehearted unity which the progressive people of 
the world admire. 
  The messages and letters express full support and solidarity 
for the struggle of the Korean people to defend the sovereignty 
of the country from the aggression moves of the imperialists and 
achieve the cause of national reunification according to the 
10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation 
advanced by President Kim Il-song. 
  Letters to him were adopted at a symposium on President Kim 
Il-song and Korean-style socialism held in Amadora, Portugal, 
and a seminar on his work held by the Nepal Institute for Chuche 
Studies. 
  The messages and letters wish President Kim Il-song good 
health and a long life. 

</TEXT>

