<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Comrade Kim Chong-il, 
Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army, sent the 70th 
birthday table to General Kim Ki-ok, a lecturer at the 
Victorious Fatherland Liberation War Museum, who is the first 
hero of the Airforce in Korea. 
  Born a son of a mountain-side tiller before the liberation, 
he learned how to operate airplanes at the Pyongyang School 
after the country was liberated as he desired and grew to be a 
full-fledged flying commander. 
  In the fatherland liberation war, he brought down with his 
propeller plane seven enemy aircrafts including two B-29s and 
two jet planes and damaged four planes. 
  He became the first hero of the Airforce in Korea for his 
exploits in battles on July 15, 1950, twenty days after the 
start of the Fatherland Liberation War. 

</TEXT>

