<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Liberalization of Service Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister on Liberalization of Service Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0605090494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0605090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In compliance with the GATT agreement, Thailand will 
not promulgate new laws or regulations to discriminate against 
foreign nationals in the service industry. Minister of Finance 
Tharin Nimmanhemin said that it is a basic commitment among 
member countries signing the General Agreement on Tariffs and 
Trade. Minister Tharin said that liberalization of service 
industry is different from other businesses. He said it 
involves licenses issued for businesses. He said the Thai 
Government plans to allow aliens to enjoy the same rights as 
Thai nationals in doing business in Thailand. He said the 
Finance Ministry will allow over five licensees of the Bangkok 
International Bank Facilities, or BIBF, to transform into 
commercial banks by 1997. 

</TEXT>

