<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Holds News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0705090794 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0705090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A news conference was held in the Ministry of 
Information and Culture [name of ministry as heard] conference 
room with the participation of deputy ministers from the 
ministry and local reporters from many news services. 
  At the news conference, Foreign Affairs Minister Somsavat 
Lengsavat briefed the participants on the rapidly changing world 
and regional situations. He also discussed the domestic 
situation in Laos and other issues; namely, the direction and 
implementation of tasks in the restructuring period. He pointed 
out that cadres and people must correctly follow the party's 
policies; hold aloft the spirit of patriotism; and cherish fine 
Lao customs, arts, and culture. He stressed that all mass media 
services and information cadres must take the initiative in 
carrying out activities in earnest to enable the multiethnic Lao 
people to understand clearly, appreciate, have confidence in 
party leadership, and engage in activities in various forms to 
fulfill the aims of restructuring. At the same time, the 
minister also discussed the foreign policy pursued by the party 
and government toward countries in this region and throughout 
the world, stressing that the Lao People's Democratic Republic 
consistently adheres to the policy of strengthening relations of 
friendship, cooperation, and mutual assistance with all 
countries in the world. 

</TEXT>

