<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Fair With Thai Cooperation Opens 4 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Fair With Thai Cooperation Opens 4 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0505114394 Vientiane KPL in English 0945 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0505114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, May 5 (KPL) -- A Lao-Thai goods 
exhibition opened in Vientiane yesterday morning. A large number 
of dignitaries attended the ceremony. 
  Among the dignitaries were Minister Phao Bounnaphon, head of 
the Prime Minister's Office, Trade Minister Sompadit Volasan, 
and Thai Ambassador Somphan Kokilanon. Members of diplomatic 
corps and international organisations to Laos were also invited 
to the opening. 
  Sisouk Sisombat, president of the National Chamber of 
Commerce and Industry, addressed the opening ceremony. He said 
that this goods exhibition was held under the cooperation 
between the Lao National Chamber of Commerce and Industry and 
the Thai Embassy in Vientiane. He pointed out that the 
objectives of the event were to contribute toward increasingly 
growing trade and cultural relations between Laos and Thailand, 
introduce the quality goods to consumers, give an opportunity to 
traders, businessmen from both countries to meet and exchange 
views on expanding their cooperation, and for the people of the 
two countries to have a cultural exchange. 
  There are 20 show rooms for Lao goods, and 30 show rooms for 
Thai goods. The Lao exhibits include handicraft items, textiles, 
jewelry, silver wares, carvings, sculptures, souvenirs, 
rattan-made furniture, wood products, and garments. The Thai 
show rooms display farm tools, sports equipment, medical 
equipment, musical instruments, educational aids, decorations, 
gifts, and others. All the goods show rooms will be kept open to 
the public till May 8. 

</TEXT>

