<F P=102>   BK0705083894 Hanoi VNA in English 0707 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0705083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 7 -- Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van 
Khai received here yesterday afternoon a delegation of the 
External Relations Committee of the parliament of the Republic 
of Korea led its chairman Chong Chae-mun now on a visit to 
Vietnam. 
  Speaking to his guests, Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van Khai 
affirmed new step of the development in the relations between 
Vietnam and the Republic of Korea (ROK) in recent years, and 
hailed the ROK's successes in the cause of renovation and 
socio-economic development in the past time, the deputy prime 
minister expressed his belief that the delegation's visit to 
Vietnam would further promote the friendship and multifaceted 
cooperation between Vietnam and the Republic of Korea. Mr. 
Chong Chae-mun, for his part, expressed his admiration at the 
great achievements recorded by the Vietnamese people in their 
cause of national construction and renovation. He said he hoped 
that Vietnam and ROK would promote the exchange of their 
experience, thus contributing to further development of the 
friendship and cooperation between the two legislatures, two 
governments and peoples. 

