<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongukyonhap Suit Against President Dismissed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongukyonhap Suit Against President Dismissed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605064794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0616 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0605064794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 6 (YONHAP) -- The Seoul district civil 
court on Friday dismissed a defamation suit filed by 
Chongukyonhap, or the National Alliance for Democracy and 
Unification, against President Kim Yong-sam. 
  Judge O Se-ip threw out the suit by the alliance, which was 
seeking 300 million won in compensation from the president for 
alleged damages caused by Kim's description of it as an 
organization sympathetic to communism during the presidential 
election campaign in 1992. 
  "The alliance, as an unincorporated association, is not 
entitled to bring a civil suit," O said. 
  "Even though the alliance had the outward appearance of 
being 
an organization with a name, an organizational network and 
operational functions, it could not be a plaintiff in a civil 
suit because it was not incorporated as an association," he said. 
  The alliance had accused Kim Yong-sam of "wrongly damaging" 
its reputation by describing its member organizations as 
followers of North Korean President Kim Il-song's "chuche" 
ideology. 
  The alliance filed the suit on Jan. 12, 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

