<H3> <TI>   Foreigners' Purchase of Stock Exceeds Sales </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreigners' Purchase of Stock Exceeds Sales </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0705035094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0223 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705035094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 7 (YONHAP) -- Foreigners have done more 
buying than selling in the Korean stock market since last week, 
securities sources said Saturday. 
  Foreigners bought shares worth 176.3 billion won and sold 
127 
billion won in stocks for a net purchase of 49.3 billion won 
between April 24 and Wednesday. 
  During the 10 days, they recorded net sales only on April 26 
at 1.3 billion won and on May 2 at 6.3 billion won. 
  In March, foreigners' net sales totaled 184.2 billion won 
and 
in the first 23 days of April, the figure came to 56.9 billion 
won. 
  Foreigners appear to be buying stocks again in response to 
reports of conspicuous signs of economic recovery and the 
perception that prices in the Seoul bourse have bottomed out. 

</TEXT>

