<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 9 (YONHAP) -- The government is expected 
to announce its official position soon on the Samsung business 
group's bid to enter the automobile manufacturing business, it 
was reported Monday. 
  A senior official at the Ministry of Trade, Industry and 
Energy said that Minister Kim Chol-su is scheduled to leave for 
Mexico next Sunday and the government is likely to announce its 
decision on Samsung before he departs. 
  Another official said that as far as he knows, "This problem 
has already been decided." 
  For the sake of formality rather than anything else, he 
added, the government is holding discussions with Samsung and 
the Chamber of Commerce in the southern port of Pusan, where 
Samsung hopes to build car manufacturing plants. 
  Samsung, one of the country's largest conglomerates, plans 
to 
submit for government approval its technology cooperation 
agreement with Nissan Motor Co. of Japan to produce passenger 
cars in Korea. 

