<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Alatas Comments on East Timor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Alatas Comments on East Timor </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Notes `Progress' in Timor Talks </H4>

<F P=102> BK0705094394 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0000 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0705094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali has praised 
the Indonesian Government for giving UN officials, human rights 
activists, officials of humanitarian organizations, and 
journalists access to East Timor. His views were disclosed by 
his spokesperson Theresa Christophe during the fourth round of 
Indonesian-Portuguese talks in Geneva, Switzerland. 
  Speaking at a news conference after the talks, Foreign 
Minister Ali Alatas said Indonesia and Portugal have made much 
progress in their efforts to create mutual trust. He said 
Indonesia has done many things to accelerate the settlement of 
the East Timor issue; for example, East Timorese have been 
allowed to see relatives in Portugal and Portuguese activists 
have been permitted to visit the former colony. 

</TEXT>

