<H3> <TI>   U.S., ROK, Japanese `Rimpac' Exercise Decried </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S., ROK, Japanese `Rimpac' Exercise Decried </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0705050794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0500 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["What is `Rimpac' Aimed At?" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- It is very ill-boding 
that the U.S. imperialists, Japanese reactionaries and South 
Korean puppets are going to stage the "Rimpac" war exercises in 
concert openly, while intensifying their conspiracy and tieup in 
an effort to stifle the DPRK on the pretext of its fictitious 
"nuclear issue", says a MINJU CHOSON commentary today, which 
reads in part: 
  The U.S. imperialists are threatening the DPRK by shipping 
into South Korea Patriot missiles and other sophisticated 
combat equipment and ceaselessly staging war exercises, big and 
small, vociferating about "international sanctions" and 
"military countermove" against the DPRK. 
  The Japanese reactionaries and other U.S.-toeing forces, 
too, 
are joining them by clamoring for "international cooperation 
system". The South Korean puppet clique broke down talks with 
the North and are leaving no stone unturned, as a shock-force, 
to stifle the fellow countrymen with the backing of outside 
forces. 
  At a time like this, the United States, Japan and South 
Korea 
are trying to stage a large-scale joint war gamble. It is only 
too clear what they seek through the gamble. 
  It proves that the U.S., Japan and South Korean 
reactionaries 
are intending to contain the DPRK militarily through their 
conspiracy and tieup under the cloak of "international 
cooperation system" and, to this end, they are substantiating 
their criminal triangular military alliance. 
  The United States and its followers are trying to destroy 
the 
DPRK, the bulwark of socialism, by driving the situation on the 
Korean peninsula into extremes militarily, but it is a foolish 
idea. 
  Should the United States and its followers persist in 
straining the situation on the Korean peninsula by staging 
"Rimpac" joint war exercises, they would be held wholly 
responsible for grave consequences arising therefrom. 

</TEXT>

