<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Humanitarian Aid To Arrive 10 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Humanitarian Aid To Arrive 10 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0505120794 Vientiane KPL in English 0943 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0505120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, May 5 (KPL) -- On May 10, 1994 at 
airport, a U.S. airlift of humanitarian supplies will be handed 
over to Lao officials and representatives of the World Vision 
for distribution in the Lao PDR [People's Democratic Republic], 
according to a USIS press release issued here yesterday. The 
equipment will be presented by U.S. Ambassador to the Lao PDR 
Victor L. Tomseth 
  The medical supplies are donated by the World Vision Relief 
and Development for its operations in Laos. The school equipment 
is a donation from the U.S. Military. The International 
Lao-American Organization donated the books. 
  This shipment is another example of assistance supplied from 
the United States to meet the humanitarian needs of the Lao 
people. 

</TEXT>

