<H3> <TI>   Senator: Spratlys Threat to National Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senator: Spratlys Threat to National Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0605085694 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0605085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Spratly Islands issue remains a threat to the 
country's security. This was the assessment made by Senator 
Orlando Mercado, chairman of the Senate Committee on Defense, 
and Arturo Enrile, chief of staff of the Armed Forces of the 
Philippines. 
  However, they expressed the hope that the prevailing tension 
would be solved by moves undertaken by the countries claiming 
the Spratlys. They added that the talks for a joint development 
of the Spratlys would help to prevent the dispute ending in 
violent confrontation. 
  [Begin recording in progress, in English] [Mercado] ...and 
the world, really, as a consequence of the demise of the Cold 
War. But, it is also an accepted notion that Spratlys or 
Kalayaan Island Group is a potential problem. 
  [Enrile] ...flashpoint is Spratlys which is (?unabated) 
because I think everybody has agreed anyway that you know 
diplomacy is still the best way to solve international disputes. 
There is really no conflict there right now, but just to 
anticipate any conflict. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

