<H3> <TI>   IAEA Not To Send Inspection Team to DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Not To Send Inspection Team to DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0605225794 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 6 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0605225794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] A spokesman for the International Atomic Energy 
Agency [IAEA] said on 6 May that the IAEA would not dispatch to 
North Korea its inspection team to observe the changing of fuel 
rods at North Korea's nuclear reactor. 
  He said: The IAEA will not send its inspection team to North 
Korea because the letter North Korea recently sent to the IAEA 
does not provide any ground for the dispatch of the inspection 
team [chosadanul pagyonhalmanhan patangul chegonghaji anko isso] 
to North Korea. 

</TEXT>

