<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister, Others Attend DBP Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister, Others Attend DBP Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805070094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
0500 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805070094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Xuan Bach] </F>
  [Text] The provincial party committee, People's Council, 
and People's Committee of Lai Chau Province held a solemn 
meeting in Dien Bien Phu [DBP] this morning to mark the 40th 
anniversary of the historic Dien Bien Phu victory. Present were 
Doan Khue, Political Bureau member and defense minister, 
representing the party Central Committee; Deputy Prime Minister 
Nguyen Khanh, representing the government; National Assembly 
Vice Chairman Phung Van Tuu; representatives of various 
departments and branches at the central level; representatives 
of Lao Cai, Son La, Yen Bai, and Hoa Binh Provinces; 
representatives of Luang Prabang and Phong Saly Provinces in the 
Lao People's Democratic Republic; and 20,000 people from various 
ethnic groups in Lai Chau. 
  Delivering a speech at the meeting, Comrade Nguyen Niem, 
member of the party Central Committee and secretary of the Lai 
Chau Province party committee, pointed out the significance of 
the Dien Bien Phu victory and the lessons of experience to be 
developed in the cause of socioeconomic construction in Lai Chau 
in accordance with the renovative spirit initiated by our party. 
  In his speech, Senior General Doan Khue reviewed the 
development of the war of resistance against the French that 
climaxed with the Dien Bien Phu campaign. As for the role and 
significance of the decisive and historic Battle of Dien Bien 
Phu, the comrade pointed out that the Dien Bien Phu victory was 
regarded as the common victory of the three peoples on the 
Indochina peninsula during their war of resistance against the 
French. The Dien Bien Phu tradition has been developed to the 
fullest, it contributed to bringing about the great victory in 
the spring of 1975, and it has helped us continue to overcome 
difficulties in building socialism successfully in Vietnam. 
  On behalf of the younger generation, Comrade Mu A Cua, 
secretary of the Lai Chau Province Youth Union, resolved to 
achieve all socioeconomic targets set by the party and state. 
  The ceremony was followed by a show-of-strength parade and a 
fitness demonstration program under the theme: Let the 
Mountains and Jungles Be Green, Fruit Orchards and Rice Fields 
Be Laden With Fruit and Panicles of Rice, and Smiles Bloom on 
Young Faces. It was designed to commemorate the 40th 
anniversary of the Dien Bien Phu victory. 

</TEXT>

