<H3> <TI>   NHAN DAN Article Marks Birthday of Karl Marx </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NHAN DAN Article Marks Birthday of Karl Marx </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0705114194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0705114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of the 176th anniversary of the 
birth of Karl Marx -- 5 May 1818 -- NHAN DAN carries an article 
by Hoang Tung entitled: A Science of Life. The newspaper says 
that Marxism- Leninism is part of the colossal treasure of 
wisdom accumulated by human society. Marxist doctrine has 
extraordinary value in the science of thinking and in the idea 
of liberating society, human beings, and thinking. Marxist 
doctrine has a long-lasting vitality. It is an open doctrine 
that has been constantly supplemented and developed, and has 
determined their path of national liberation, regained their 
independence and freedom, and taken the initiative in renovating 
their socialist thinking. It has increased production toward 
the goal of building a prosperous people, powerful country, and 
civilized society. We must firmly grasp the science of thinking 
and the pattern of national development so as to bring 
Vietnamese thinking to a new level on the basis of our guiding 
ideology: Marxism-Leninism and Ho Chi Minh Thought. 
  To study Marxism is to study his scientific method of 
thinking and struggle to follow his example in dedicating our 
whole life to our lofty cause. 

</TEXT>

