<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nong Duc Manh Meets Scientists To Review Tasks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nong Duc Manh Meets Scientists To Review Tasks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0905090494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0905090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 7 May, at the Vietnam Scientific-Technological 
Associations Union Office in Hanoi, Comrade Nong Duc Manh, 
member of the party Central Committee Political Bureau and 
chairman of the National Assembly held a working session with 
representatives and members of various scientific-technological 
associations. 
  After hearing scientists, representing more than 300,000 
members of the union, report on the activities and achievements 
of the union during the past period as well as its measures 
aimed at creating favorable conditions for 
scientific-technological associations to carry out their tasks 
effectively, Comrade Nong Duc Manh commended the union members 
for their efforts and high sense of responsibility. He highly 
appraised the role and position of the intelligentsia 
representing various scientific-technological associations in 
Vietnam. He said that these people have engaged in research and 
diversified tasks which have positively contributed to the 
renovation process. He expressed the hope that various 
scientific-technological associations would draw on experiences 
and conduct more creative research to improve scientific 
projects and apply scientific-technological innovations to the 
socioeconomic development program, thereby contributing to 
building the law-governed state of the people, by the people, 
and for the people. 
  He also called on these associations to positively 
participate in the struggle against hunger and poverty, thus 
contributing to implementing the objectives of making our people 
prosperous, our country powerful, and our society just and 
civilized. 

</TEXT>

