<H3> <TI>   Minister Sawit Visits Burma for Energy Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Sawit Visits Burma for Energy Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0705122894 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0705122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister to the Prime Minister's Office Sawit 
Phothiwihok is leading a 20-member delegation to Myanmar [Burma] 
during 5 and 8 May for talks on energy cooperation. Minister 
Sawit will negotiate the purchasing price of Myanmar natural gas 
to be supplied to the Petroleum Authority of Thailand from 
Myanmar's (Yedana) field in the Gulf of Martaban. Discussion 
with the Myanmar side will also touch on bilateral cooperation 
in tourism, investment, and water source development. The Thai 
delegation will call on Myanmar leaders and meet Thai investors 
there. 
  Meanwhile, the Myanmar Government this week released 30 
Thais 
mainly fishermen jailed in that country. The ceremony to free 
the Thais was held at the Victoria Point and in the presence of 
the Thai delegation. The release was made with the good 
relations between Thailand and Myanmar taken into account. 

</TEXT>

