<H3> <TI>   Burma Urged To Regulate Natural Gas Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burma Urged To Regulate Natural Gas Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0905120994 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0905120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Thailand has asked Myanmar [Burma] to regulate the 
prices of its natural gas export in line with fuel oil prices. 
  During his meeting with Myanmar Minister of Energy U Khin 
Maung Thein, Minister to the Prime Minister's Office Sawit 
Phothiwihok told the Myanmar minister that Thailand plans to 
utilize natural gas supply from Myanmar at the power plant in 
Rat Buri Province in the central plain bordering Myanmar. 
  He explained that the power plant can use either fuel oil or 
natural gas and that higher prices of natural gas would not be 
acceptable. 
  The Thai minister also informed his Myanmar counterpart that 
Thailand has also contracted to buy energy from the Lao People's 
Democratic Republic and Malaysia. Moreover, the government has 
allowed the private sector to participate in power generation. 
He said Thailand could not afford to buy fuel at higher prices 
from Myanmar. 

</TEXT>

