<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   MITI Resumes Underwriting Trade Insurance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MITI Resumes Underwriting Trade Insurance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0905100794 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 May 94 
Morning Edition p 7--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0905100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Nobuyuki Sakai] </F>
  [Text] Warsaw, 6 May -- During a meeting on 6 May, 
Minister of International Trade and Industry [MITI] Eijiro Hata 
officially informed Polish Foreign Economic Relations Minister 
Leslaw Podkanski of the partial resumption of underwriting 
investment insurance for Poland, which has been suspended since 
1991. Japan will resume guaranteeing insurance related to 
investments and short-term (less than two years) trade insurance 
from 15 May. Hata is visiting Poland to attend the East-West 
Economic, Industry, and Trade Ministers Conference. It was also 
decided that Japan would send experts to Poland as advisers to 
help the Polish Government implement its industrial development 
policy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

