<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata Seeks Cooperative Ties With LDP, SDPJ </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Seeks Cooperative Ties With LDP, SDPJ </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0905140394 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 9 May 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0905140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata commented on future 
Diet steering on 8 May, saying: "When I think of the situation 
Japan is in, I feel that we have to approve the budget as soon 
as possible. We need not only reforms, but also cooperation with 
other parties." It seems that his remark indicates that Hata 
decided he has no choice but to seek cooperation with the 
Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] and the Social Democratic Party 
of Japan [SDPJ] over the issue of the draft for redrawing 
single-seat electoral districts for the House of Representatives 
and other issues to approve the fiscal 1994 budget, which is the 
most urgent task. 
  On his responsibility as a person who appointed former 
justice minister, the prime minister stated: "By doing some 
soul-searching regarding the past history, Japan will candidly 
apologize for what it did and teach next generations. We will 
show our resolve by exerting efforts to prevent tragedies like 
war." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

