<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 6, IRNA -- Iranian Ambassador to 
Australia [Mohammad] Ruhisefat in a meeting with Australian 
Foreign Minister Gareth Evans in Canberra today exchanged views 
on regional and international issues as well as on human rights. 
  Evans referred to Iran's importance in the history of world 
civilization and said the Islamic Republic should have a greater 
role in international issues. 
  He added that his country was independent and adopted 
decisions based on its own national interests. 

