<H3> <TI>   Evans Opens 16th ASEAN-Australia Forum in Canberra </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Evans Opens 16th ASEAN-Australia Forum in Canberra </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0305053494 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0100 GMT 3 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0305053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia's foreign affairs minister, Gareth Evans, 
has opened an ASEAN-Australia forum in Canberra, predicting 
continued growth in links between ASEAN and Australia. It is 
the 16th ASEAN-Australia Forum and is being attended by more 
than 100 government officials and representatives of business. 
  Senator Evans told the forum he expects the growing 
relationship between Australia and the region to intensify over 
the next two years. 
  [Begin Evans recording] The trend in ASEAN-Australia 
relations is already clear. By 2014 we will be, I believe, 
significantly closer than even we are today, and forming 
something of a cohesive unit within a broader Asia-Pacific 
framework. 
  In a changing regional environment, I think we need to look 
to the future of ASEAN-Australia relations and develop further 
the structures and the linkages to sustain our political and 
economic relationship into the next century. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

