<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Training Accord Signed With Singapore </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Training Accord Signed With Singapore </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805071394 Singapore THE STRAITS TIMES in English 7 May 94 
p 30 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore THE STRAITS TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The armed forces of Singapore and the Philippines 
will carry out regular joint military exercises and training. 
  A memorandum of understanding (MOU) formalising the training 
arrangement, as well as co-operation between the two sides, was 
signed between the Armed Forces of the Philippines (AFP) and the 
Singapore Armed Forces [SAF] on Thursday. 
  The signing of the MOU took place at the Department of 
Foreign Affairs Building in Manila between Mr. Roberto R.Romulo, 
the Philippine Secretary of Foreign Affairs and Mr. Tan Seng 
Chye, Singapore's Ambassador to the country. 
  Anoa-Singa 2/94 will be the first exercise which will be 
held 
following this newly signed agreement. 
  It will be conducted here from May 12-18. 
  Under the Anoa-Singa series, regular joint land exercises 
will be held between the two armed forces, with the venue 
alternating between the countries. 
  The first exercise under this series took place last year in 
the Philippines. 
  Thursday's MOU is, however, not the SAF's first training 
agreement with the AFP. 
  Under an earlier one concluded in 1979, the Republic of 
Singapore Air Force [RSAF] was allowed to deploy regular 
training detachments at the Clark Air Base. 
  The RSAF ceased this deployment only when the eruption of 
Mount Pinatubo in 1990 made the air base inoperable. 
  The air force agreement expired subsequently, in December 
1991. 
  The Ministry of Defence said that the signing of the new MOU 
affirmed the friendly relations existing between the two 
countries and their long-term commitment to closer defence ties 
and co-operation between the SAF and the AFP. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

