<H3> <TI>   Infrastructure Projects Announced for Cordillera </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Infrastructure Projects Announced for Cordillera </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1005020094 Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 5 May 94 p 
b-18 </F>

<F P=103> BK1005020094 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila MANILA BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Emily R. Pena] </F>
  [Text] The Department of Interior and Local Government 
(DILG) announced yesterday the implementation of infrastructure 
projects, worth P [Philippine peso] 21.621 million, in five 
provinces in the Cordillera Autonomous Region (CAR). 
  In a report submitted by the Department of Public Works and 
Highways (DPWH) to the DILG, it was noted that the multi-million 
project enrolled by DPWH under the Kabuhayan [Livelihood] 2000 
program of President Ramos is designed to increase agricultural 
productivity in the region. 
  Among those provinces which will benefit from the project 
are 
Abra, Kalinga-Apayao, Benguet, Ifugao and Mt. Province. 
  Engineer Jose C. Guanzon, DPWH project manager, said the 
improvement of roads and water supply construction projects 
using labor-based/equipment-supported (LB/ES) methods will 
accelerate development in CAR areas specifically, in terms of 
generating more employment among the people here. 
  In Abra, the Pigidian-Abra-Ilocos Sur road is being 
concreted 
while water supply structure will be constructed in 
Villaviciosa, Laplapog, and in Lagayan, Pang-ot and in other 
selected municipalities in Benguet. 
  Improvement of drainage and road concreting will also be 
undertaken in Bokod, Benguet-Viscaya road, and in Mankayan, 
Abatan, and Mankayan-Cervantes in Benguet. 
  Meanwhile, the DPWH has also identified municipalities in 
Kalinga-Apayao, Ifugao and Mt. Province that will be included in 
its infrastructure program under Kabuhayan 2000. 
  DILG heads the steering committee of Kabuhayan 2000, a 
program of the government which aims to generate more job 
employment and opportunities in the countryside within three 
years. 

</TEXT>

